    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-floor offensive profile anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker**, who represent our premier plays with scores of 83.29 and 78.73, respectively. **Gunnar Henderson** occupies the lead-off spot against Roupp, benefiting from an elite park factor and a significant dynamic platoon advantage. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** is positioned to feast against Rocker; his projection is bolstered by favorable wind conditions and a strong order placement. **Jackson Merrill** also provides elite value (75.10) as he faces the soft-tossing Sugano, leveraging a superior SP skill matchup that elevates his run-production potential.\n\nWhile our lineup is deep, the decision to bench **Nolan Schanuel** was the tightest call of the morning. His score of 47.94 fell just short of the 50-point threshold required to displace our current starters, as he faces a formidable matchup against Burns, whose low xERA drags down the entire offensive ceiling. We are keeping a close watch on **Miguel Vargas**, who holds a marginal 51.96 score; he carries a 31% rain risk in his contest against Bubic, and his value is further suppressed by a lack of speed upside compared to our bench options. We remain cautious with **Heliot Ramos** and **Andy Pages**\u2014despite their lower order spots, their ability to exploit slow opposing deliveries for stolen bases remains a critical component of our strategy to capture the scarce SB category.",
